WEBVTT

00:06.881 --> 00:09.426
The thing about living
with time travel,

00:09.426 --> 00:10.969
it's never your only problem.

00:10.969 --> 00:13.221
You get all
the normal problems too.

00:18.059 --> 00:19.227
Like, for instance...

00:24.441 --> 00:25.525
her friends.

00:27.485 --> 00:28.903
- Hi.
- Hey.

00:33.116 --> 00:36.035
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:47.046 --> 00:48.506
Thanks.
Yeah.

00:54.220 --> 00:58.349
- So, how's Clare?
- Good, she's good. Yeah.

00:58.433 --> 00:59.768
- Same old Clare.
- Yeah.

01:11.279 --> 01:13.615
- Charisse?
- Good, yeah.

01:13.615 --> 01:14.908
We've gotta ask, right?

01:14.908 --> 01:16.701
Because if we don't,
when we get back to them

01:16.785 --> 01:17.744
they're gonna ask, yeah?

01:17.744 --> 01:18.995
Charisse will ask,
"How's Clare?"

01:18.995 --> 01:20.288
Clare will ask,
"How's Charisse?"

01:20.288 --> 01:22.165
And if we don't ask,
we're in trouble. Am I right?

01:22.165 --> 01:23.666
Well, they live
in the same apartment.

01:23.750 --> 01:25.210
They probably
know how each other are.

01:25.210 --> 01:26.336
Yeah. Good point.

01:28.463 --> 01:29.839
I-- I was kind
of joking, really.

01:29.923 --> 01:31.800
- Right. Sure.
- Observational humor.

01:31.800 --> 01:33.343
Got you! Yeah.

01:38.890 --> 01:40.558
Why do you look at me like that?

01:40.642 --> 01:42.185
- Like what?
- I don't know. Like that.

01:42.185 --> 01:43.144
Like what?

01:43.228 --> 01:44.896
You've always given me
funny looks.

01:46.815 --> 01:48.900
- You're a time traveler.
- I'm aware.

01:48.900 --> 01:51.736
You're the first interesting
thing that ever happened to me.

01:51.820 --> 01:53.363
I mean, I'm a lawyer.

01:53.363 --> 01:55.782
I'd literally get paid
to prevent interesting things

01:55.782 --> 01:57.492
from happening.
And now look at me.

01:58.409 --> 02:00.161
I'm friends
with a time traveler.

02:00.245 --> 02:02.747
- Are you, though?
- Am I what?

02:02.831 --> 02:04.624
You and me,
are we actually friends?

02:04.624 --> 02:05.917
Well, according to you we are.

02:05.917 --> 02:07.335
According to me,
what does that mean?

02:07.335 --> 02:08.711
Well, not you you,
you from the future.

02:08.795 --> 02:12.006
- What does he know?
- Hell of a lot more than you.

02:13.925 --> 02:15.218
You know,
It just doesn't seem like

02:15.218 --> 02:16.261
we've got a lot in common,

02:16.261 --> 02:17.720
- you know what I'm saying?
- Mm-hmm.

02:17.804 --> 02:20.056
Yeah. I mean,
apart from the obvious.

02:20.056 --> 02:21.224
- The obvious?
- Yeah.

02:21.224 --> 02:22.934
Apart from the fact
we both want to fuck Clare.

02:23.810 --> 02:25.687
No! No, no, that-- that is not--

02:25.687 --> 02:26.855
- That is in no way true.
- Relax!

02:26.855 --> 02:28.231
- It's okay.
- I want you to understand

02:28.231 --> 02:29.357
that that is no way true.

02:29.357 --> 02:32.026
It's fine, it's fine,
I get it. All right.

02:32.110 --> 02:33.152
I mean, do anything about it,

02:33.236 --> 02:34.529
and I'll tie a knot
in your windpipe,

02:34.529 --> 02:38.491
but, uh, short of that,
I graciously accept the tribute

02:38.575 --> 02:40.076
of your debilitating envy.

02:40.827 --> 02:42.120
Cheers.

02:45.248 --> 02:47.750
- You need to take that back.
- It's not a problem, man.

02:47.834 --> 02:49.794
- You need to apologize.
- HENRY DETAMBLE, 28: For what?

02:49.878 --> 02:51.296
I don't have feelings
of that kind

02:51.296 --> 02:53.131
or of any kind for Clare.

02:53.131 --> 02:55.466
- Oh, sure you don't.
- You should apologize!

02:55.550 --> 02:56.759
You should sit back down
on your ass

02:56.843 --> 02:58.261
before it starts talking again.

03:00.346 --> 03:02.682
All right, we tried to have
a drink, it didn't work.

03:02.682 --> 03:03.933
Let's just leave it at that.

03:04.893 --> 03:06.102
Listen.

03:06.102 --> 03:08.271
If you think that I'm giving you
funny looks the whole time,

03:08.271 --> 03:10.023
maybe there's a reason
that you don't know about.

03:10.023 --> 03:11.733
Oh, if you're gonna put
your hand on my knee,

03:11.733 --> 03:13.067
maybe you should buy
me dinner first.

03:13.151 --> 03:16.237
- I've seen you before.
- I know. I was drunk.

03:18.156 --> 03:19.574
- Before that.
- Before when?

03:19.574 --> 03:21.618
- That wasn't the first time.
- HENRY, 28: Oh, when was it then?

03:21.618 --> 03:23.745
- I recognized you.
- Where from?

03:23.745 --> 03:26.748
Hmm, see, if we had been having
a pleasant drink,

03:27.457 --> 03:28.917
maybe I'd have told you!

03:39.886 --> 03:43.348
♪ ("TIME TRAVELER'S WIFE"
THEME MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

05:24.073 --> 05:25.283
Can I have a rest?

05:25.283 --> 05:27.493
Rest from what?
You're just sitting.

05:32.248 --> 05:34.167
- Can I see it?
- Not yet.

05:37.295 --> 05:38.796
I hope you remember
I'm wearing clothes.

05:40.131 --> 05:41.090
How did you know?

05:41.174 --> 05:42.592
Well, I've seen
the finished picture.

05:43.676 --> 05:44.677
That's cheating.

05:44.761 --> 05:46.721
Well, so is drawing me
without any clothes.

05:50.641 --> 05:52.602
- What was that?
- Nothing.

05:53.436 --> 05:54.562
A squirrel or something.

05:54.562 --> 05:56.064
What makes you think
I don't know exactly

05:56.064 --> 05:58.232
- who that was?
- It was nobody.

05:58.316 --> 06:00.193
I've met your family, remember.

06:02.820 --> 06:03.946
Long time ago.

06:06.783 --> 06:07.825
Why are you smiling?

06:09.452 --> 06:12.497
- Well, I guess it was funny.
- What was funny about it?

06:12.497 --> 06:13.873
HENRY, 38: You.

06:13.873 --> 06:15.458
- Me?
- HENRY, 38: Yeah.

06:15.458 --> 06:19.796
You, Clare Abshire.
You're very, very funny.

06:29.764 --> 06:32.225
Do you hate your parents,
or something?

06:32.225 --> 06:34.435
No, of course not.
Why would I hate them?

06:34.519 --> 06:36.646
You seem to have moved
a very long way away from them.

06:40.483 --> 06:42.276
Are we gonna
be there soon?

06:42.360 --> 06:43.444
It's not far.

06:50.785 --> 06:53.538
Sit back. Relax.
What's wrong with you?

06:54.622 --> 06:55.665
I'm in a car.

06:55.665 --> 06:57.500
CLARE ABSHIRE, 20:
Okay, what's wrong with cars?

06:57.500 --> 06:59.418
Me. I'm what's wrong.

06:59.502 --> 07:00.545
If I time travel now,

07:00.545 --> 07:03.005
wherever I arrive,
I'll be doing sixty.

07:03.089 --> 07:05.174
Somewhere in history,
there'll be a big splat

07:05.258 --> 07:06.926
with a surprised-looking face
in the middle.

07:22.900 --> 07:24.569
Your phone keeps buzzing.

07:24.569 --> 07:26.529
- Yeah.
- But you don't answer it.

07:26.529 --> 07:27.947
Yeah, it's nothing.

07:27.947 --> 07:30.616
Careful. I might start thinking
it's your other woman.

07:31.701 --> 07:33.452
Well, it is.

07:34.078 --> 07:37.373
- Ingrid?
- No. Gomez.

07:37.373 --> 07:41.043
- Gomez?
- Yeah we had a, uh, little tiff.

07:41.127 --> 07:42.628
Well, he's just trying
to be friendly.

07:42.712 --> 07:44.547
Well, he needs to stop that.

07:44.547 --> 07:46.299
He's gonna be
your best friend okay,

07:46.299 --> 07:47.717
like it or not.

07:47.717 --> 07:50.094
- Says who?
- Says future you.

07:50.178 --> 07:51.637
You don't want to listen to him.

07:51.721 --> 07:53.556
I am well known
for being a lying asshole.

07:53.556 --> 07:55.975
Well, future you isn't.
Future you is awesome.

07:55.975 --> 07:57.476
Could you stop preferring me
to my face?

07:57.560 --> 08:00.730
He's you but awesome,
how could I not prefer him?

08:00.730 --> 08:02.023
Oh, great. Perfect.

08:02.023 --> 08:03.816
There's exactly one of me
in the world

08:03.900 --> 08:05.818
and I'm coming second.

08:05.902 --> 08:07.236
I mean, is there anything
I do better?

08:07.320 --> 08:10.406
What about the-- the hair?
Is the hair any better?

08:10.406 --> 08:14.285
The sex is good.
I really like the sex.

08:14.285 --> 08:17.622
Oh, well, that's, uh, good.
Thank you for the feedback.

08:17.622 --> 08:19.999
Well, I mean, I'm basically
betraying the love of my life

08:19.999 --> 08:23.502
with his hot kid brother,
but... it's good.

08:23.586 --> 08:26.380
Well, you put it like that
and it does sound good. Thanks.

08:32.637 --> 08:33.679
Gomez?

08:33.763 --> 08:34.805
- Yeah.
- Answer it.

08:34.889 --> 08:37.016
- Do I have to?
- Yes. And be nice.

08:38.226 --> 08:40.269
Hey.

08:40.353 --> 08:42.897
- Hey there, comrade.
- Comrade.

08:42.897 --> 08:44.815
<i>So, you're on
the road then, with Clare.</i>

08:45.524 --> 08:46.567
Everything going okay?

08:46.651 --> 08:48.402
Yeah sure.
<i>No time travel issues?</i>

08:48.486 --> 08:50.529
HENRY, 28: <i>Well I showed up
in Dallas in '63,</i>

08:50.613 --> 08:51.572
and shot up a motorcade.

08:51.656 --> 08:53.115
I hope I didn't change
anything important.

08:53.199 --> 08:56.077
- Joking, right?
- Yeah, I'm joking.

08:56.077 --> 08:58.246
I gotta get used to you
and your sense of humor.

08:58.246 --> 09:00.331
Well, that would save
a certain amount of time.

09:00.331 --> 09:03.000
- Hey listen, yesterday?
- HENRY, 28: <i>Ah, forget about it.</i>

09:03.084 --> 09:04.377
I'm sorry I blew up at you.

09:04.377 --> 09:06.170
It's fine.
We were both out of order.

09:06.254 --> 09:07.672
I'm totally happy
to forget about it.

09:08.172 --> 09:10.007
- Me too.
- Good.

09:11.342 --> 09:12.551
Oh, um,

09:12.635 --> 09:15.137
and, uh, the other thing I said
about seeing you a while back,

09:15.221 --> 09:17.848
<i>how I recognized you
the first time I saw you.</i>

09:17.932 --> 09:19.725
Mm-hmm
<i>Is it, um...</i>

09:21.435 --> 09:23.396
Is it okay to tell you
about that?

09:23.396 --> 09:25.481
- HENRY, 28: <i>Yeah sure it is.</i>
- It like...

09:26.524 --> 09:28.609
It doesn't affect causality?

09:29.610 --> 09:30.778
Sorry, what?
Let's go.

09:30.778 --> 09:34.031
Well, does-- does telling you
affect the causality

09:34.115 --> 09:37.034
- you know, of time.
- The causality of time?

09:37.994 --> 09:39.537
Do you--

09:39.537 --> 09:41.497
do you listen to the words
coming out of your mouth,

09:41.497 --> 09:43.624
or do you just hang around
in the same room as them?

09:43.708 --> 09:45.251
<i>You know what, Henry?</i>

09:46.002 --> 09:47.003
Fuck you, man!

09:47.003 --> 09:49.171
No, no, no, wait, wait.
I'm joking, man. I'm--

09:50.756 --> 09:52.008
Again, I'm joking.

09:52.967 --> 09:55.720
We don't like each other.

09:55.720 --> 09:57.346
How is he supposed
to be my best friend

09:57.430 --> 09:59.598
if we don't like each other?

10:01.892 --> 10:03.144
I don't like him.

10:03.144 --> 10:04.854
But he's gonna be
your best friend.

10:04.854 --> 10:08.107
How? How's that even possible?

10:10.735 --> 10:13.946
Well. There it is.
There's where I come from.

10:14.030 --> 10:16.073
- Meadowlark House.
- HENRY, 28: Okay.

10:17.241 --> 10:19.952
Big. I'd say, uh, big.

10:20.036 --> 10:21.954
It's weird to think
you've never seen it.

10:22.038 --> 10:23.331
HENRY, 28:
One family in this place.

10:23.331 --> 10:24.999
What do you need
all the other rooms for?

10:25.750 --> 10:27.251
Our issues.

10:29.378 --> 10:31.547
CLARE, 34: <i>The trouble
with revisiting your childhood</i>

10:31.547 --> 10:34.717
<i>is nothing is quite
where you left it.</i>

10:34.717 --> 10:37.345
<i>You tell yourself it all looks
exactly the same</i>

10:37.345 --> 10:39.597
<i>and then somebody else sees it.</i>

10:56.072 --> 10:58.532
That's Mark. Promise
you won't out-asshole him.

10:58.616 --> 11:00.534
Well, it's not like
it's a competitive thing.

11:00.618 --> 11:01.619
Promise?

11:01.619 --> 11:03.120
- I promise.
- Thank you.

11:03.204 --> 11:08.209
There she is.

11:08.209 --> 11:10.711
So, this is the young man
in question, is that right?

11:10.795 --> 11:14.590
Mom, Dad, Mark,
this is Henry DeTamble.

11:14.590 --> 11:15.633
Good to meet you.

11:15.633 --> 11:17.676
- Call me Philip.
- Ah! I'm Lucille.

11:17.760 --> 11:20.137
- Please, welcome to our home.
- Lucille, hi.

11:20.221 --> 11:22.348
Sorry, did you say Mom?
How's that possible?

11:22.348 --> 11:24.475
How is this your mom?
What, were you eleven?

11:24.475 --> 11:28.145
Oh! Don't be silly.

11:28.229 --> 11:30.231
So, you're the lucky guy
who's been violating

11:30.231 --> 11:33.484
- my kid sister, yeah?
- Yeah, well, you know...

11:35.111 --> 11:36.153
one of them.

11:38.656 --> 11:40.449
- Uh. That's for you.
- Thank you.

11:40.533 --> 11:41.492
- Yes.
- Yes.

11:41.492 --> 11:43.786
- Please. Come on in.
- Yes, yes, let's go.

11:43.786 --> 11:46.205
So, Clare tells us you work
at the Newberry Library.

11:46.205 --> 11:48.040
HENRY, 28: Yeah, the Newberry,
that's right.

11:48.124 --> 11:51.127
- You're a librarian.
- Yes. Special collections.

11:51.127 --> 11:52.294
Ah.

11:52.378 --> 11:54.422
So,
what are your long-term plans?

11:54.422 --> 11:56.757
- Philip.
- What?

11:56.841 --> 11:58.342
HENRY, 28:
Pretty much that, you know.

11:58.426 --> 11:59.885
Books aren't going anywhere.

12:01.011 --> 12:02.054
Okay.

12:05.057 --> 12:06.976
You ever been to the Newberry?

12:06.976 --> 12:08.894
Sometimes we take clients there.

12:08.978 --> 12:10.312
Corporate events. My law firm.

12:10.396 --> 12:12.356
Oh, right, yeah, Clare said
you're a lawyer. That's cool.

12:12.940 --> 12:13.941
Yeah, for my sins.

12:18.195 --> 12:19.447
My friend's a lawyer. So,

12:19.447 --> 12:22.158
that's basically...
...two lawyers that I know.

12:22.158 --> 12:24.702
- Three. Also a lawyer.
- Almost a lawyer.

12:24.702 --> 12:26.245
Basically a lawyer.

12:26.245 --> 12:28.080
Well, a couple of lawyers
in the family, huh?

12:28.164 --> 12:30.249
Hmm. Yes. We're very proud.

12:30.249 --> 12:33.586
And that's gotta come in handy,
right? If anyone breaks the law.

12:37.131 --> 12:39.592
I don't--
I don't think we would.

12:39.592 --> 12:41.177
Not that you ever would.
I just mean,

12:41.177 --> 12:43.345
there's-- there's a safety net.

12:43.762 --> 12:45.055
Uh...

12:45.139 --> 12:46.348
If you ever wanted to...

12:47.600 --> 12:48.809
cut loose.

12:53.772 --> 12:55.524
- What's your friend's name?
- What friend?

12:55.608 --> 12:58.277
- Your lawyer friend.
- Oh, yeah, Gomez.

12:58.277 --> 13:00.362
Jeff Gomez?
Oh, no, he's in Kentucky now.

13:00.446 --> 13:02.198
What's-- what's his full name?
I might know him.

13:02.198 --> 13:03.824
I know a lot of the young ones.

13:05.910 --> 13:09.830
Just, uh... Gomez.
We call him Gomez.

13:13.918 --> 13:15.211
- Hey, there.
- It's Gomilinsky.

13:15.211 --> 13:16.587
Gomilinsky, good to meet you.

13:16.587 --> 13:20.216
No! No, that's-- No,
Gomez is short for Gomilinsky.

13:20.216 --> 13:22.718
It's sort of like a nickname.
Jan Gomilinsky.

13:22.718 --> 13:24.053
- HENRY, 28: Right.
- We call him Gomez.

13:24.053 --> 13:25.721
- Yeah, forgot that.
- CLARE, 20: Uh-huh.

13:26.597 --> 13:28.182
You forgot his name?

13:28.182 --> 13:32.019
Yeah, you know, sometimes
you forget your friends, uh...

13:32.019 --> 13:33.229
...names.

13:38.609 --> 13:42.488
So, this is you. The blue room.
Uh, bathroom's through there.

13:42.488 --> 13:46.033
- I'm gonna get you some towels.
- There's nothing blue in here.

13:46.033 --> 13:48.410
It used to be blue.
The name stuck.

13:49.453 --> 13:52.206
- Where's your room?
- Why?

13:52.206 --> 13:54.208
Oh, I just wanted to see it.

13:54.208 --> 13:56.919
And memorize the route,
so I can find it in the dark.

13:57.962 --> 13:58.963
Come on.

14:01.298 --> 14:03.384
We seem to be a very long way
from each other.

14:03.384 --> 14:05.594
Can't imagine what my parents
were thinking.

14:13.477 --> 14:14.478
Wow.

14:22.152 --> 14:23.153
HENRY, 28: Oh.

14:24.822 --> 14:26.782
- Is that the meadow?
- Yeah.

14:26.782 --> 14:29.034
And on the other side
are the woods, and in the woods

14:29.118 --> 14:30.911
is the clearing
where we're gonna meet.

14:31.328 --> 14:32.413
Oh.

14:32.413 --> 14:34.206
God, it's so weird
you don't know that.

14:37.084 --> 14:39.169
- Smaller than I thought.
- What is?

14:39.253 --> 14:41.255
The meadow.
I thought it'd be bigger.

14:42.423 --> 14:45.175
Um, it seemed big to me.

14:45.259 --> 14:48.762
But then I suppose everything's
bigger when you're little.

14:49.638 --> 14:51.098
Bigger and more important.

14:54.810 --> 14:56.103
But you, uh,
you've been back there

14:56.103 --> 14:57.313
since you were a kid, right?

14:57.313 --> 15:00.441
Yeah, but, you know,
seeing it through your eyes now.

15:00.441 --> 15:03.819
Can we go see it?
The clearing in the woods.

15:06.614 --> 15:08.741
Maybe, yeah, after lunch.

15:10.618 --> 15:11.619
Maybe?

15:12.536 --> 15:14.455
- Uh, sensing a problem.
- No.

15:15.873 --> 15:16.915
What?

15:20.002 --> 15:22.171
It's just...

15:22.171 --> 15:23.380
Just what?

15:24.506 --> 15:25.591
It's the clearing.

15:26.634 --> 15:28.761
Yeah.

15:30.429 --> 15:32.848
The clearing was our place.

15:35.517 --> 15:37.061
As in, our place.

15:37.061 --> 15:39.438
- CLARE, 20: Well, yes.
- As in, I'm him.

15:39.438 --> 15:40.981
Clare, I'm the man
you met there.

15:41.065 --> 15:42.650
- Yes, I know.
- It's me, Clare.

15:42.650 --> 15:44.276
I'm Henry. The same Henry.

15:45.444 --> 15:46.445
Someday.

15:50.908 --> 15:52.368
You don't like me being here,
do you?

15:54.203 --> 15:56.121
Like this place belongs
to the other me.

15:56.205 --> 15:59.208
- That's stupid.
- Yeah, it is. But is it true?

16:01.460 --> 16:03.921
You could always try
to be nice to me, you know.

16:03.921 --> 16:05.881
It could become a habit.
Like, a thing we do.

16:07.800 --> 16:10.177
- I win.
- What? You beat me again.

16:10.177 --> 16:12.262
- I'm getting better.
- No, you're not.

16:15.182 --> 16:16.475
I am nice.

16:16.475 --> 16:18.352
Yeah, but you keep looking
disappointed that I'm not him.

16:18.352 --> 16:19.728
Well, you keep not being him.

16:19.812 --> 16:21.063
Apparently, I'm gonna get there.

16:23.232 --> 16:26.068
Don't you ever think
how amazing it must be

16:26.068 --> 16:28.237
to fall in love
in the right order?

16:31.281 --> 16:32.616
Call me sentimental, but I...

16:34.118 --> 16:37.413
think it has some pretty
amazing qualities right now.

16:37.413 --> 16:39.665
- Careful.
- HENRY, 28: Sorry.

16:39.665 --> 16:41.917
Don't just throw my things.

16:41.917 --> 16:43.460
You really like checkers
that much?

16:43.544 --> 16:46.380
Yeah, I used to play checkers.
This is the set I used with him.

16:46.380 --> 16:47.464
With you.

16:49.800 --> 16:51.301
