33:33.678 --> 33:35.763
Yeah, really badly.
Made a real mess of myself.

33:35.847 --> 33:37.348
Yeah, it was a bad fall.
It was very bad.

33:37.432 --> 33:39.308
Well, then why
didn't you say something?

33:39.392 --> 33:40.935
- I forgot.
- Forgot?

33:40.935 --> 33:43.771
Yeah, she forgot.
You know, because of the fight.

33:43.855 --> 33:45.565
Oh, we weren't fighting.
There was no fight at all.

33:45.565 --> 33:47.024
We never really fight,
do we, Clare?

33:47.108 --> 33:48.109
No, we were fighting,

33:48.109 --> 33:49.819
- I was just explaining.
- Okay.

33:49.819 --> 33:51.654
Mm-hmm. I was, uh,
being judgmental.

33:51.738 --> 33:53.448
Remember how
I was being judgmental?

33:53.448 --> 33:54.782
Yeah, Clare was just saying
about that.

33:54.866 --> 33:56.242
Yeah, I was just saying
that, uh,

33:56.242 --> 33:58.202
you know, that's why I felt bad.

33:58.286 --> 34:02.415
Because I forgot about the fall.

34:02.415 --> 34:03.833
Right. Of course.

34:03.833 --> 34:05.960
I mean, it wasn't really
a fight, just...

34:09.297 --> 34:11.174
So, Henry,
what about your parents?

34:11.174 --> 34:12.967
Clare hasn't really
mentioned them.

34:12.967 --> 34:15.636
Probably forgot.

34:15.720 --> 34:17.555
Uh, well, my dad plays violin

34:17.555 --> 34:19.724
for the, uh,
Chicago Philharmonic.

34:19.724 --> 34:21.601
Oh, my goodness,
that's amazing. Really?

34:21.601 --> 34:23.352
We've been
to the Chicago Philharmonic.

34:23.436 --> 34:24.645
- More than once.
- Yes, we must have

34:24.729 --> 34:25.688
seen your father then.

34:25.772 --> 34:27.231
Yeah. I guess
you would have. Yeah.

34:27.315 --> 34:29.442
Oh, that's so impressive.

34:29.442 --> 34:31.444
Is he, um, the first violinist?

34:31.444 --> 34:34.405
- No, just a violinist.
- And what about your mother?

34:35.823 --> 34:37.283
Uh, my mother died
when I was young.

34:37.283 --> 34:39.577
- Oh, dear, I'm so sorry.
- Yeah, she was a singer.

34:39.577 --> 34:40.953
Worked with my dad.

34:41.037 --> 34:43.539
His mom
was Annette Lyn Robinson.

34:43.623 --> 34:45.583
No! Really?

34:45.583 --> 34:48.169
- Really?
- Yeah. She was quite something.

34:48.169 --> 34:50.171
Oh, she was extraordinary.

34:50.171 --> 34:52.340
We actually have several
of her recordings here.

34:52.340 --> 34:54.175
You know who that is,
don't you, Philip?

34:54.175 --> 34:57.053
Yes, of course.
She was a remarkable performer.

34:57.053 --> 34:58.054
Remarkable woman.

34:58.054 --> 34:59.722
Well I thought so,
but she was my mom.

34:59.806 --> 35:01.557
But this-- this soup,
I mean, wow.

35:01.641 --> 35:04.352
It's, uh-- Smells delicious.
Sorry I delayed it all

35:04.352 --> 35:07.897
- by falling over like an idiot.
- You know, Alicia is a cellist.

35:07.897 --> 35:10.149
- I'm a hairdresser.
- Alicia plays the cello.

35:10.233 --> 35:11.317
It's always been her dream.

35:11.317 --> 35:13.528
No, I'm a hairdresser.
I like being a hairdresser.

35:14.403 --> 35:16.781
Excuse me, I have a question.

35:16.781 --> 35:19.575
You were late down here because
you fell over in the shower--

35:19.659 --> 35:21.118
I think
we've covered this, Mark.

35:22.745 --> 35:23.913
So, when did you have the fight?

35:23.913 --> 35:25.039
Does it matter?

35:25.123 --> 35:26.541
Well, you said
the fight made you forget

35:26.541 --> 35:29.418
about Henry hurting himself.
So it must have been after it,

35:29.502 --> 35:31.754
but I don't see
how there was time.

35:31.838 --> 35:34.382
We're not in court, Mark.
Are we in court right now?

35:36.676 --> 35:37.844
I don't do court work.

35:37.844 --> 35:39.554
I just don't see when
you could have had the fight.

35:39.554 --> 35:41.222
Well, we didn't have a fight.

35:41.222 --> 35:43.307
I was being judgmental,
that's all.

35:43.391 --> 35:45.893
A little bit critical.
Now leave it.

35:50.398 --> 35:52.233
Henry's father
could give you lessons.

35:52.233 --> 35:53.860
I'm sorry.
He's a violinist.

35:53.860 --> 35:55.570
He could teach you lessons,
don't you think?

35:55.570 --> 35:56.779
In hairdressing?
Does he do that?

35:56.863 --> 35:58.489
He could get you back
on track, Alicia.

35:58.573 --> 36:01.576
I am on track.
I'm doing something I'm good at.

36:01.576 --> 36:03.578
Why do you keep going on
about the cello which I sucked.

36:03.578 --> 36:06.205
Because a mother is allowed
to be proud of her daughter.

36:06.289 --> 36:08.040
The cellist and the artist.

36:08.124 --> 36:09.208
I'm an art student, Mom.

36:09.292 --> 36:10.793
That's not being proud,
that's being disappointed.

36:10.877 --> 36:12.503
It's not being disappointed
to know that a person

36:12.587 --> 36:14.130
- could do better.
- Yes it is.

36:14.714 --> 36:16.299
You're bleeding.

36:17.300 --> 36:18.301
Oh.

36:19.260 --> 36:21.262
Sorry about that. Yeah.

36:21.262 --> 36:24.098
Uh, thought I'd got all that.

36:27.018 --> 36:28.978
Don't worry,
I've, uh, cleaned up.

36:28.978 --> 36:30.271
All good as new.

36:33.149 --> 36:34.442
Okay.

36:35.443 --> 36:38.112
Just, uh, so I'm clear.

36:38.112 --> 36:40.656
You're lying there
on the bathroom floor,

36:40.740 --> 36:42.199
naked and bleeding,

36:42.283 --> 36:44.994
and somehow at this moment,
Clare becomes

36:44.994 --> 36:47.246
a bit too critical.

36:47.330 --> 36:49.749
And then she just leaves
you there,

36:49.749 --> 36:52.376
forgets the entire incident
but, nonetheless, has some

36:52.460 --> 36:56.923
vague memory that she might
have been a bit judgmental.

36:59.050 --> 37:01.594
- That about it.
- Fuck off.

37:02.762 --> 37:05.640
- Really. Just fuck the fuck off.
- Mm-hmm.

37:05.640 --> 37:07.433
CLARE, 20: You know what
I've had enough of?

37:07.433 --> 37:11.938
Everything! Mom,
your daughter is a hairdresser

37:11.938 --> 37:13.356
and she is perfectly happy
about it,

37:13.356 --> 37:15.441
and that is totally fine.

37:15.441 --> 37:17.526
Your other daughter
is an art student,

37:17.610 --> 37:19.070
which means she better get good
at bank robbery

37:19.070 --> 37:22.114
because sorry, everyone,
she's gonna marry a librarian.

37:22.198 --> 37:23.908
And your one and only son

37:23.908 --> 37:25.451
is a such
a total fucking asshole,

37:25.451 --> 37:27.995
he did the impossible
and became a lawyer

37:28.079 --> 37:29.914
without getting
noticeably worse.

37:29.914 --> 37:31.916
These are things
you have to deal with.

37:31.916 --> 37:33.501
Thank you for the fucking soup.

37:43.511 --> 37:44.512
Excuse me.

37:53.854 --> 37:55.189
Did she say marrying?

37:59.485 --> 38:00.486
Clare?

38:02.571 --> 38:03.948
Clare, you there?

38:03.948 --> 38:06.325
- Henry.
- Hey.

38:07.576 --> 38:10.329
It's okay.
There's a thing you can do.

38:22.133 --> 38:23.175
Shit.

38:24.635 --> 38:25.761
Where is she going?

38:29.265 --> 38:30.474
She's looking for me.

39:09.013 --> 39:10.056
CLARE, 34: <i>When you're young</i>

39:10.056 --> 39:11.557
<i>you see only what
you want to see.</i>

39:12.683 --> 39:15.061
<i>Nothing gets in the way
of the fairy tale.</i>

39:36.082 --> 39:39.460
<i>When you grow up,
your vision clears,</i>

39:39.460 --> 39:41.921
<i>and you see so much less.</i>

39:59.522 --> 40:03.818
They're all right, really,
my mom and dad. Even Mark.

40:04.860 --> 40:07.279
They're just, you know, people.

40:09.031 --> 40:10.950
Takes way to long
to realize that, doesn't it?

40:11.867 --> 40:13.327
Your mom and dad
are just people.

40:17.790 --> 40:20.793
She took it to Chicago with her,
when she was missing you.

40:25.756 --> 40:26.841
You know, if you'd asked me,

40:26.841 --> 40:28.884
I could have put some concealer
on those bruises.

40:31.262 --> 40:32.346
Can you help me?

40:33.764 --> 40:34.765
Help you what?

41:02.585 --> 41:03.627
HENRY, 28: Clare?

41:07.548 --> 41:09.300
Guess this place
means nothing to you.

41:11.802 --> 41:13.554
Don't you even get déjà vu?

41:17.141 --> 41:18.559
I was going make a big ceremony

41:18.559 --> 41:21.312
of bringing you out here
for the first time. Sorry.

41:22.813 --> 41:24.023
HENRY, 28: It doesn't matter.

41:26.108 --> 41:27.109
I'm here now.

41:28.569 --> 41:29.570
Yeah.

41:37.036 --> 41:38.078
I'm here now.

41:50.257 --> 41:52.635
So, what do you think?

41:54.011 --> 41:55.346
She's pretty good, your sister.

42:02.645 --> 42:05.189
Are you gonna tell me
what you think?

42:07.483 --> 42:09.401
CLARE, 12: I don't have
any friends called Henry.

42:09.485 --> 42:11.362
HENRY, 28: That's okay.
I promise you, I'm a friend.

42:11.362 --> 42:12.696
CLARE, 12:
Have you seen dinosaurs?

42:12.780 --> 42:14.406
I tickled
a dinosaur's tummy once.

42:14.490 --> 42:15.491
Do you have a wife?

42:15.491 --> 42:16.867
Funnily enough,
her name's Clare.

42:16.951 --> 42:18.077
- Like me.
- I'm gonna disappear.

42:18.077 --> 42:19.411
Can I watch?

42:19.495 --> 42:21.205
- CLARE, 12: <i>Are you coming back?</i>
- HENRY 32: <i>Yeah,</i>

42:21.205 --> 42:22.289
<i>I'll be back lots of times.</i>

42:22.373 --> 42:24.124
CLARE 13: <i>I have
stupid ideas sometimes.</i>

42:24.959 --> 42:26.293
And your wife's called Clare?

42:26.377 --> 42:27.461
I think you're married to me.

42:27.461 --> 42:29.255
HENRY, 32: <i>We're not married
in the future.</i>

42:31.048 --> 42:33.550
CLARE, 13: <i>You could be
out there somewhere, dying.</i>

42:33.634 --> 42:35.970
<i>- Somewhere in time.</i>
- Hello, Henry.

42:35.970 --> 42:37.221
<i>You've never kissed me,
you know.</i>

42:37.221 --> 42:39.181
Oh, I've kissed
you a million times.

42:39.265 --> 42:41.141
CLARE, 18:
<i>Why do I always have to wait?</i>

42:41.225 --> 42:42.142
Let it happen.

42:42.226 --> 42:43.477
You were asking me a question.

42:43.477 --> 42:44.728
HENRY, 41: <i>Clare Abshire...</i>

42:46.730 --> 42:47.856
will you marry me?

42:59.785 --> 43:02.538
You asked me a question
in this clearing once, or...

43:03.455 --> 43:04.581
you're going to.

43:05.749 --> 43:07.459
And I never got round
to answering.

43:08.836 --> 43:10.045
And what was the question?

43:10.129 --> 43:11.338
Well, the answer is yes.

43:12.881 --> 43:14.842
Yes. Oh, my God, yes.

43:15.926 --> 43:17.344
And I'm sorry.

43:17.428 --> 43:20.848
- For what?
- I loved you from the start.

43:20.848 --> 43:23.225
From the moment I met you
in that stupid library,

43:23.309 --> 43:25.185
I was completely
in love with you.

43:25.269 --> 43:27.271
I just expecting someone else.

43:28.022 --> 43:29.064
Well, that's okay.

43:30.065 --> 43:33.610
I can do that.
I can be somebody else.

43:54.798 --> 43:57.259
♪ ("TIME TRAVELER'S WIFE"
THEME MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
